A = final amount after n years ($1225)
P = principal amount invested ($1000)
r = annual interest rate (we want to find this)
n = number of years (3)

Rearrange the formula to solve for r:

r = (A/P)^(1/n) - 1

Plug in the values:

r = (1225/1000)^(1/3) - 1
= (1.225)^(1/3) - 1
≈ 1.0507 - 1
≈ 0.0507

To convert this to a percentage, multiply by 100 and round to the nearest integer:

r ≈ 5%

So, the final answer is:
